Name: Sakati-Nyhan syndrome
Definition: An acrocephalosyndactylia characterized by abnormalities in the bones of the legs

Name: Pfeiffer syndrome
Definition: An acrocephalosyndactylia that has_material_basis_in mutations in the FGFR1 and FGFR2 gene which results_in premature fusion located_in skull.

Name: Greig cephalopolysyndactyly syndrome
Definition: An acrocephalosyndactylia that has_material_basis_in mutation in the GLI3 gene which results_in abnormal development located_in limb

Name: Saethre-Chotzen syndrome
Definition: An acrocephalosyndactylia that has_material_basis_in a genetic mutation in the TWIST1 gene which results_in premature fusion located_in skull.
